article.headline: Alabama State 71, Tulane 59
article.story: EL PASO, Texas (AP) -- Taylor Rochestie scored 19 points and sank 7-of-7 free throws to lead Tulane to a 71-59 win over Alabama State on Tuesday in the Sun Bowl tournament. Tulane, which was down 34-28 at the end of the first half, came back by outscoring Alabama State 43-25 in the second half. Marcus Kinzer and Donnie Stith each had 11 points for Tulane (5-5), while Quincy Davis had 10. Kevin Spicer led Alabama State (2-7) with 16 points. He was followed by George Savage with 11 and Ralfeal Golden with 10. Tulane shot 38 percent for the game, while Alabama State shot 29 percent.
